de_id": "464e2583-7002-4bb6-8bb6-8b867fb760ef", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "48c88b47f2b280b043cd1bd42d81e7baf9d907313a86db03d2dd3b340f0d176a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "29f46d3e-e1f1-4b0b-a19a-c927cc6c7dee", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "e7fdd466ffab6fdb99e4a1d713b4c735433debac94bc62ea99608d79661715e4", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "\u00be\n\nProject Schedule:\n\n\u0083 Complete Design: Summer 2021 \u0083 Begin Construction:\n\n Summer/Fall 2021\n\nBirdview Avenue Improvements (CalOES Project)\n\n\u00be Updates:\n\n\u0083 The  design  of  this  project  has  been  included  in  the  Malibu  Park Drainage  Improvements  project  and  updates  will  be  provided  under that project.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 6792, "end_char_idx": 7109, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "29f46d3e-e1f1-4b0b-a19a-c927cc6c7dee": {"__data__": {"id_": "29f46d3e-e1f1-4b0b-a19a-c927cc6c7dee", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e823ee32-181f-4f48-a3e5-49e477087d22", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a818b63515b498dd8936a3aaabe94c1239af084b8446c19a30a8bb1b8eafdb04", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "582e716e-99d6-4b2f-8908-eea13d4026fe", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "22e2daabc8d0b9fe67da76c570573822515425101173c896e960061971e32dad", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "8f2ecf54-0f21-4908-9d61-1ed9d6c89dbc", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "7336cb576290ce1838903133c1ecc71788bfd1ab4d55214ad8b1cafefd5ef481", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "Outdoor Warning Sirens (FEMA Project)\n\n\u00be Updates:\n\n  This project will be funded through a grant from FEMA after the Wooley Fire.  The project consists of hiring a consultant to develop a plan that includes  the  evaluation  of  a  siren  system  and  possible  locations.    Staff  is working on an RFQ to hire a consultant for the design.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 7111, "end_char_idx": 7451, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "8f2ecf54-0f21-4908-9d61-1ed9d6c89dbc": {"__data__": {"id_": "8f2ecf54-0f21-4908-9d61-1ed9d6c89dbc", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e823ee32-181f-4f48-a3e5-49e477087d22", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a818b63515b498dd8936a3aaabe94c1239af084b8446c19a30a8bb1b8eafdb04", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "29f46d3e-e1f1-4b0b-a19a-c927cc6c7dee", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "e7fdd466ffab6fdb99e4a1d713b4c735433debac94bc62ea99608d79661715e4", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "bb2213ae-ecb2-4bed-90f2-48a8b8a8f0f2", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "b2606c7b550f9bb44da04312c090c42dbd5818e2091e36ad9fec3de939c97953", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "\u00be Project Schedule: \u0083 Complete Design: Unknown\n\nDisaster Projects (Construction)\n\nNone at this time\n\nDisaster Projects (Completed) Guardrail Replacement Citywide (FEMA Project)\n\n\u00be Project  Description:\n\n    This  project  consisted  of  replacing  the  damaged guardrail throughout the City as a result of the Woolsey Fire.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 7453, "end_char_idx": 7776, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "bb2213ae-ecb2-4bed-90f2-48a8b8a8f0f2": {"__data__": {"id_": "bb2213ae-ecb2-4bed-90f2-48a8b8a8f0f2", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e823ee32-181f-4f48-a3e5-49e477087d22", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a818b63515b498dd8936a3aaabe94c1239af084b8446c19a30a8bb1b8eafdb04", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "8f2ecf54-0f21-4908-9d61-1ed9d6c89dbc", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "7336cb576290ce1838903133c1ecc71788bfd1ab4d55214ad8b1cafefd5ef481", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "df024941-354c-4bcd-a54e-d2eb3907213c", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "8944b513f99a14f1f9f555e7f8ba63be5d802a96a4f7799bdaad5ae69566799c", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "Corral Canyon Road Bridge Repairs (FEMA Project)\n\n\u00be Project Description:\n\n  This project consisted of replacing fire damaged existing fencing and repairing the damaged embankment adjacent to the bridge.\n\nCorral Canyon Culvert Repairs (FEMA Project)\n\n\u00be Project Description:\n\n  This project consisted of replacing a portion of Corral Canyon Road that was damaged from a failed storm drain.Page 5 of 6\nAgenda Item # 4.A.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 7778, "end_char_idx": 8195, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "df024941-354c-4bcd-a54e-d2eb3907213c": {"__data__": {"id_": "df024941-354c-4bcd-a54e-d2eb3907213c", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e823ee32-181f-4f48-a3e5-49e477087d22", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a818b63515b498dd8936a3aaabe94c1239af084b8446c19a30a8bb1b8eafdb04", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "bb2213ae-ecb2-4bed-90f2-48a8b8a8f0f2", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "b2606c7b550f9bb44da04312c090c42dbd5818e2091e36ad9fec3de939c97953", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "284d21e6-b41f-4ff6-9234-7e90d41c12df", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "9d3697c0df6a2553435b60ceb57e054a23d0f788791742601e69c9e177b2b40d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "Disaster Projects (Not Started)\n\nClover Heights Storm Drain (FEMA Project)\n\n\u00be Project Description:\n\n  This project consists of design and construction of a few storm drains on Clover Heights.  The existing storm drain facility ends at the intersection  of  Clover  Heights  and  Harvester  Road.    During  storms,  this intersection floods and causes debris to block the road.  An extended storm drain towards the end of Clover Heights will help eliminate this issue.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8197, "end_char_idx": 8665, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "284d21e6-b41f-4ff6-9234-7e90d41c12df": {"__data__": {"id_": "284d21e6-b41f-4ff6-9234-7e90d41c12df", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e823ee32-181f-4f48-a3e5-49e477087d22", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a818b63515b498dd8936a3aaabe94c1239af084b8446c19a30a8bb1b8eafdb04", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "df024941-354c-4bcd-a54e-d2eb3907213c", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "8944b513f99a14f1f9f555e7f8ba63be5d802a96a4f7799bdaad5ae69566799c", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "518ae6bc-c506-43ae-bf9d-6c48ac59bc72", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "d6753bfd12bb25374ba36ba104d62a3060661f635e6924f2874d83a5d38e86bb", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "\u00be Estimated Schedule:\n\n\u0083 Complete Design: Spring 2022\n\n\u0083 Begin Construction: Summer 2022\n\nLatigo Canyon Road Culvert Repairs (FEMA Project)\n\n\u00be Project Description:\n\n  This project consists of repairing the existing storm drain on Latigo Canyon Road located approximately 2,500 feet from PCH that was damaged by the Woolsey Fire.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8667, "end_char_idx": 8995, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "518ae6bc-c506-43ae-bf9d-6c48ac59bc72": {"__data__": {"id_": "518ae6bc-c506-43ae-bf9d-6c48ac59bc72", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "e823ee32-181f-4f48-a3e5-49e477087d22", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a818b63515b498dd8936a3aaabe94c1239af084b8446c19a30a8bb1b8eafdb04", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "284d21e6-b41f-4ff6-9234-7e90d41c12df", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "9d3697c0df6a2553435b60ceb57e054a23d0f788791742601e69c9e177b2b40d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "5b38d46f-c079-461c-b63c-e1eab09b401b", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "f103a00ccecd21d4a7bde940c83cd2e7a59a6a907187c94201e9c71bd59f3153", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "\u00be\n\nEstimated Schedule: \u0083 Complete Design: Winter 2021\n\n\u0083 Begin Construction: Spring 2022\n\nEncinal Canyon Road Drainage Improvements (CalOES Project)\n\n\u00be Project Description:\n\n  This project consists of repairing damage storm drain facilities and roadway embankments that were damaged by the Woolsey Fire.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8997, "end_char_idx": 9300, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "5b38d46f-c079-461c-b63c-e1eab09b401b": {"__data__": {"id_": "5b38d46f-c079